  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The primary purpose of this study is to assess the prevalence of asymptomatic chronic angle
      closure in high risk Caucasian individuals, namely those with hyperopia. A secondary purpose
      is to assess whether specific demographic or ocular-anatomic parameters in this population
      are associated with a higher risk for angle closure.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Caucasian subjects aged &gt; 40 years with hyperopia will undergo complete eye examination
      including subjective refraction and gonioscopy. In addition we will measure axial length,
      anterior chamber depth and lens thickness using ultrasound biometry.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
